# ============================================================
# Noisy Dueling Double-DQN with CNN
# Runs: Variant 0 (800/100/100) then Variant 1 (800/100/100)
#
# SPEED FIX (requested):
#   - Removed ALL model.predict(...) calls
#   - Replaced with direct forward passes:
#       self.model(x, training=False).numpy()
#   This avoids predict() overhead (huge CPU speedup).
#
# Dufference to mitderm code:
#applies PER importance-sampling weights inside the loss, i.e. each transitionâ€™s Huber loss is multiplied by is_w; Code A samples with PER but trains as if samples were uniform.

# trains only on the selected action Q(s,a) using a custom GradientTape step; Code A updates the full Q-vector by overwriting one entry and calling train_on_batch.

# updates PER priorities from TD-errors produced by the same weighted training step, ensuring consistency; Code A computes TD-errors separately from numpy Q-values after the update.

#uses a cleaner, correct SumTree leaf lookup and an in-place soft target update, reducing overhead and avoiding subtle priority indexing errors.
# ============================================================

